name: Either
desc:
A container class that represents one of two possible values.
An Either instance is either a Left value, or a Right value.
This class has supporting functions for void types, however it's use is against spec

name: conditional
desc: Returns the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise returns the result of the provided function

name: flatMap
desc: Applies a function to the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise returns the current Either

name: flatMapLeft
desc: Applies a function to the value on the left of the Either if it exists, otherwise returns the current Either

name: fold
desc: Applies one of two provided functions to the value of the Either, depending on its state

name: get
desc:
Shorthand for getOrThrow
Returns the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise throws Left value as an error
Don't use this on Right of void

name: getLeftOrElse
desc: Returns the value on the left of the Either if it exists, otherwise returns the provided default value

name: getLeftOrThrow
desc: Returns the value on the left of the Either if it exists, otherwise throws the provided exception

name: getOrElse
desc: Returns the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise returns the provided default value

name: getOrThrow
desc: Returns the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise throws the left value unless an exception is provided

name: getRightOrThrowLeft
desc: Attempts to get R but will throw left value as an error if the right value does not exist

name: isLeft
desc: Returns true if this Either instance is a Left value.

name: isRight
desc: Returns true if this Either instance is a Right value.

name: Either.left
desc: Constructs an Either instance with a left value.

name: left
desc: Returns the left value of this Either instance.

name: map
desc: Maps the value on the right of the Either using a provided function

name: mapLeft
desc: Maps the value on the left of the Either using a provided function

name: mapLeftVoid
desc: Maps the value on the left of the Either using a provided function when right is a void type

name: Either.right
desc: Constructs an Either instance with a right value.

name: right
desc: Returns the right value of this Either instance.

name: throwIfLeft
desc: Throws if value is of type left, otherwise does nothing

name: toOption
desc: Converts the Either to an Option, returning the value on the right of the Either if it exists, otherwise None

name: toOptionLeft
desc: Converts the Either to an Option, returning the value on the left of the Either if it exists, otherwise None

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: Either.unit
desc: Constructs an Either instance with a right generic value of Unit.

desc: A string representation of this object.

name: swap
desc: Swaps the left and right values of an Either.

name: buildSimpleGroupMintingTransaction
desc:
Builds a simple transaction to mint Group Constructor tokens.
If successful, the transaction will have a single input (the registrationUtxo) and a single output (the minted
group constructor tokens).

name: buildSimpleLvlTransaction
desc: Builds a simple lvl transaction with the given parameters

name: buildSimpleSeriesMintingTransaction
desc:
Builds a simple transaction to mint Series Constructor tokens.
If successful, the transaction will have a single input (the registrationUtxo) and a single output (the minted
series constructor tokens).

name: buildTransferAllTransaction
desc:
Builds a transaction to transfer the ownership of tokens (optionally identified by tokenIdentifier). If
tokenIdentifier is provided, only the TXOs matching the identifier will go to the recipient. If it is null, then
all tokens provided in txos will go to the recipient. Any remaining tokens in txos that are not transferred to the
recipient will be transferred to the changeLockAddress.

name: buildTransferAmountTransaction
desc:
Builds a transaction to transfer a certain amount of a specified Token (given by tokenIdentifier). The transaction
will also transfer any other tokens (in the txos) that are encumbered by the same predicate to the change address.
